   "author_association" : "NONE",
   "body" : "Giving the C++ Standard Committee control of the public interface of your type means they will break it. C++23 adds a new `allocate_at_least` member to `std::allocator`. Very bad things happen when, say, `std::vector` uses `allocate_at_least` from `secure_allocator`'s base to allocate memory which it then tries to free with `secure_allocator::deallocate`.\r\n\r\n(Discovered by microsoft/STL#3712, which will be reverted by microsoft/STL#3819 before it ships.)",
